I've only just decided to jump on the body spec bandwagon, which means at 26 my mind is at 14, and body at 21 +2. This means that until about 45, I'll always be one body dd behind.  <IMG SRC="frown.gif" border="0"><P>I'm trying to practicise soloing techniques, and I'm finding it kinda tough. My roots last 40 seconds, so I can only effectively cast it twice to get my kill in, otherwise its down to 10s and that aint that much time to backup and nuke.<P>This seems to work best outside in open areas. I'm working on yellow con moor boogeys (with a pet by my side as backup). I root, str/con debuff, nuke,nuke,root,run to new spot, dd,dd,dd,quickcast dd (hopefully its dead). If it resists once tho I have problems.<P>I tried this in darkness falls. Big mistake. There just isn't enough room to manouver without pickuping up something else that wants to nip at your heels.<P>So the question is this. How do *you* hunt effectively in dungeons with little manouvering space and aggro mobs?<P>--------------------<P>Cheynos - 32 Sorcerer<BR>Severim - 35 Friar<BR>Qaug - 24 Infil<BR>Kalessin - 13 Cabalist<BR>Team Alpha Strike Force, Tristan
