<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Mezzing won't work since the mob will be damaged - below 90% hits (i think, might be 80%), you can no longer mez something.<P>That soloing technique sounds very tough, same as a wizard but with worse range and damage. You run the serious problem of getting a resist with your root.<P>You can try a few variations ...<P>Root - debuff - dd - dd - amnesia - pet - run - wait - dd - dd - dd etc<P>Root - debuff - dd - dd - confusion   <IMG SRC="wink.gif" border="0"> - see what happens<P>I have found that confusion buys you plenty of time usually, with the mob running around aimlessly (always goes north) in between hitting you.<P>However, my recommendation is to stick enough in mind (20?) to get an even con pet, then use the tried and trusted (and very safe) pet method. You only get the even con pet to 40 but beyond that things change anyway. Now that pets regenerate health so fast this is a good way of soloing. In fact, if you can get a good spawn you can take groups of 2 yellow or 3 blue safely and make nealy as much xp as you can in a good group.<P>--------------------<P>Yosarian<BR>Sorcerer lvl 40<BR>Dragon's Shadow Guild - Nimue
</FONT>
