<HR size="1" color="#12350C">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Soloing in dungeons isn't tough if you give yourself a bit of open space to work with, it becomes tricky in places like keltoi and some spots in the barrows, but in darkness falls it's a breeze, you just need to work on your technique and find what's comfortable for you. There are really 3 basic variations you can use for body soloing.<P>1). No pet and just nuking.<P>     This is the most dangerous and generally should be avoided unless there are no pets nearby enough to be convenient and you don't feel like chasing confused critters. It works best against monsters that have a negative energy resist as you generally won't need as many blasts to finish them.<BR>     You start with blasting, never start with a root, it only wastes a step in the diminishing returns for duration, your debuffs aren't going to have a noticeable effect on the fight if your not using a pet and your using body dd's. Then another blast, then you root, which gives you enough time for a follow up root(generally you will not see consecutive root resists, for those rare occasions you do, you can either be brave and blow your qc, or just start running). Then you back up to max spell range again, and continue. If your keeping body spec up equal with mind, you shouldn't be needing more than 6-7 blasts to finish something off as you get older, so you basically have dd,dd,root,dd,dd, if you've got a critical anywhere along the line, you might try another dd then qc'ing a final one to finish it, or play it safe with another root. At level 47 I could sometimes finish yellow lesser telamons in 5 casts if i got a decent crit, so a second root usually was not necessary.<P>2). Nuking with pet<P>    This is the safe and cowardly way to play it, virutally no risk at all unless you fall asleep at the keyboard or get smited with the random yellow/orange mob that will resist 4 straight amnesias. You can do this in two ways, either start out blasting, then amnesia as the mob approaches you and let the pet start hitting it a bit before finishing, or start out with the pet fighting, then nuke away after your pet draws a decent amount of aggro. With the new uberhealing pets the latter example here is the safer way to go, since you dont have to be concerned with how beat up the pet gets during a fight, only that it survives. If you do the former though, remember that amnesia is a straight 2 second casting time spell, so if your persistent(e.g. spamming the key) you can even get a cast off in melee if you do get unlucky with resists.<P>3). Nuking with confusion<P>     This is something i'd never recommend in a dungeon unless you were extremely bored. It works best outdoors, and even better when your near a lot of other npc's. You start off with a root, then confuse, and blast away. This method is better if you decide to solo reds because confuse resists dont break root, and root generally will not be resisted very often. If you wanted to be extremely super safe you could also have a pet nearby in case it was the unluckiest day of your life and the monster you pulled resisted all 4 roots(if you can't get 4 roots off from max range you shouldn't be soloing).<P>All three of those methods *can* work in dungeons, though if your realistically trying to level, stick to the first two. Hope this helps =)<P>--------------------<P>Shalandra Ilveyorn<BR>Sorceress of 47 seasons on Percival
</FONT>
