Unless you intend to forever forgo an even con pet and the level 34 ae mez, stay with your second choice there and get 20 mind. Yes more points in body will decrease your variance and result in more overall damage, but not enough to warrant losing pets. <P>And if your looking at it for rvring, its really not that big a deal, from what i've seen, getting near or exceeding your level in skill only puts you at a zero variance on even cons, your still going to get *some* variance if your blastings things higher than you, so unless your just going to totally forgo your other spell lines, there's no need to overdo it beyond getting a specific spell.<P>--------------------<P>Shalandra Ilveyorn<BR>Sorceress of 47 seasons on Percival
