Soloing in a dungeon without a pet is suicide.  You may do well for awhile, but you will get resists and then you will die and lose all the exp you just got.<P>Since the mob regen patch, pets are amazing.  It is the only way to solo now, in my opinion.  Sure the pet takes exp, but when the pet can regen health faster than you regen mana, how can you go wrong?<P>One thing that I have noticed in RvR, is that when I have a pet, assassins seem to leave me alone.  That is not to say they won't kill you, but they will normally bypass me and hit the wizzies or theurgists standing nearby.<P>--------------------<P><B>Gyles</B>-Level 46 Sorcerer<BR><B>Lydon Sharpe</B>-Level 41 Mercenary<BR><B>Brief Encounter</B>-Level 23 Scout<BR>Defenders of the Mithril Tower<BR>Galahad Server
