"Good group" is the key phrase thre Caxus. Yes in a good group exp will be faster but soloing has a lot of merits, for one you don't have to pay attention when your soloing. I can kill yellow's with a pet while i'm reading a book or cleaning my house and not even helping it, for another it saves you the trouble of actually having to find said "good group", and for a lot of people it's just the way they would rather play, and if you did a side by side comparison, someone soloing oranges consistently would be right up there with exp gained over time against someone in a good group, and with probably half the stress and interaction required, so don't knock it =).<P>And also there's no need to make mind sorcs sound like they have any kind of an advantage over any other type soloing, any template with 32 mind will be able to solo efficiently, be it body/mind, matter/mind, body/matter/mind, etc.<P>--------------------<P>Shalandra Ilveyorn<BR>Sorceress of 47 seasons on Percival
