Comment on the "good group" post.<P>I'm finding I'm soloing more these days with my characters. Why? Mainly because it's too much effort to find that good group. I like being able to sit back and bring in the xp soloing - knowing that I am totally responsible for whether I die or not (for the most part), and can stop and start when I choose.<P>Too many bad pulls/calls in group situations have made me wary of groups. My attitude is generally to give a group one chance, and if it fux up, I'll go play somewhere else.<P>This game is about fun and stress-relief. Many groups are the opposite of that.   <IMG SRC="mad.gif" border="0"><P>--------------------<P>Cheynos - 32 Sorcerer<BR>Severim - 35 Friar<BR>Qaug - 24 Infil<BR>Kalessin - 13 Cabalist<BR>Team Alpha Strike Force, Tristan
